<p>Games and sports play a vital role in shaping the overall development of an institution. From improving physical fitness to promoting social skills, there are several reasons why MHSK prioritizes athletics. Engaging in physical activities helps develop strong bones, muscles, and improves overall health  while also providing students with a valuable outlet for stress, building mental toughness and resilience.</p>

<p>Sports and games also promote social skills, teamwork, and communication. In team sports like basketball, soccer, or volleyball, players must work together and communicate effectively to achieve their goals. Additionally, sports teach students about the importance of discipline and hard work  essential life skills that apply far beyond the playing field.</p>

